The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Ten nailed for riots

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Patna, May 9: A Bhagalpur court today found 10 of the accused in one of the cases of communal riots guilty of brutally killing five people, all from the minority community, on October 14, 1989.

 Additional district and sessions judge (VII) Navneet Kumar Pandey is expected to pronounce the mode of punishment on May 12.

 So far, about 200 hundred people have been awarded punishment in various cases related to one of the worst communal riots since Independence. 

 In the present case, five persons were killed at Kamarganj village under Sultanganj police station. A total of 23 persons had been made accused but during the trial the court acquitted 13 of them due to lack of evidence. 

 Those killed in the present case were Mohammad Zafar, Mohammad Kalam, Mohammad Sauf, Mohammad Mehboob Alam and Mohammad Basheer.

 The accused include Dhruv Bhagat, Arun Mandal, JaiJai Yadav, Tarkeshwar Yadav, Ram Vilas Yadav, Hari Kishore Yadav, Naro Yadav, Siya Ram Yadav, Raj Kishore Yadav and Saryug Yadav.




